b':camera: credit: @adwoabeauty 16oz but performs like 32 :OK_hand_medium-dark_skin_tone:here are a few tips to maximize your experience with our products:
\xe2\xa0\x80
moisturizing curl defining cream \xe2\x80\x94 can be used on wet, damp, or dry hair. however we recommend to apply on wet hair for the best definition + moisture:sweat_droplets: don\xe2\x80\x99t be fooled by the consistency. purposely made thinner to speed up air drying time and absorption into your twists, braids and wash n go\xe2\x80\x99s. contains organic honey + beeswax for moisture and locks in your definition, you do NOT need to add gel on top. go in very light on each section and enjoy days of lasting curls. note: over applying will result in stiffness.
\xe2\xa0\x80
deep conditioning treatment \xe2\x80\x94 this is the foundation for moisturized hair. apply weekly, on wet hair in sections, and detangle from tip to root. please note: heat is not mandatory for use, however, if you have very dry hair and want deeper penetration, add heat with a heat cap and/or a hooded dryer. if you\xe2\x80\x99re having issues with product buildup, incorporate steam treatments 1-2x\xe2\x80\x99s a month, max.
\xe2\xa0\x80
moisturizing curl defining gel \xe2\x80\x94 apply on sopping wet hair AND rewet the sections as you work the product through. warm the product in your hands to break it down before applying. rake/shingle/praying hands method each section of hair. if the product begins to curdle (this is normal), rewet the sections and work the product INTO your stands:old_key:. it will dry clear. note: this is due to the high oil + butter contents in this gel product (which is not typical) and occurs when the oils sits and solidifies :woman_scientist_medium-dark_skin_tone:. as with all gels, there is a cast. allow the cast to break on its own (about 24 hours) to avoid unwanted additional frizz. gel cast protects the hair from the elements (wind and dust pollution) while your curls dry and \xe2\x80\x9cset\xe2\x80\x9d. *see tutorials on this product before use*
\xe2\xa0\x80
our products provide a healthy, comfortable hold. they are not formulated to provide a strong hold. strong hold = high %\xe2\x80\x99s of (drying) alcohols. :exploding_head:
\xe2\xa0\x80

b'We\xe2\x80\x99re constantly in awe of @patmcgrathreal\xe2\x80\x94from her out-of-this-world, totally mesmerizing formulas to her fearlessness as a makeup artist, CEO, and founder. b'High-performance formulas. Gender-neutral approach. Diverse representation. @adwoabeauty is the kind of modern hair-care company we\xe2\x80\x99re proud to put on our shelves :green_heart:\xe2\xa0\x80
\xe2\xa0\x80
\xe2\x80\x9cadwoa beauty is a prestige, gender-neutral, clean, modern, diverse brand for diverse people. It is important for me to showcase the diversity in black beauty and change the way that 80% of the population of black people see themselves and their kinky hair traditionally represented. \xe2\xa0\x80
\xe2\xa0\x80
We built an ecosystem where our products are formulated, manufactured, packaged and shipped by people that look like me. We were also intentional about creating highly effective products to perform on hair types from kinky to wavy, rather than from wavy to curly, as is the norm. We represent the black beauty consumer in a new way with simple, clean, soft imagery backed by amazing products.\xe2\x80\x9d'

b'Journeys like @adwoabeauty founder Julian Addo\xe2\x80\x99s keep us inspired and remind us of the work we have to do to represent more Black entrepreneurs in the beauty industry. We\xe2\x80\x99re proud to support Julian and her company :red_heart_selector: #15PercentPledge\xe2\xa0\x80
\xe2\xa0\x80
\xe2\x80\x9cI don\xe2\x80\x99t think you can understand how much of my purpose, my community and this brand means to me. Immigrant. Raised by a single mom in NYC project housing. The movie title of my life would be: \xe2\x80\x98Don\xe2\x80\x99t be so quick to throw people away.\xe2\x80\x99 \xe2\xa0\x80
\xe2\xa0\x80
I immigrated to the United States at two and a half years old with my family from Liberia. I worked in a salon at 14 years old and enrolled in vocational high school to practice and study cosmetology. I opened my first salon at 21 years old.\xe2\xa0\x80
\xe2\xa0\x80
Looking back, I can\xe2\x80\x99t truthfully say that hair was my passion\xe2\x80\x94I was just naturally really good at it. Hair, however, was the vehicle that led me to my passion. Listening to, mentoring, and empowering other black women during some of the most vulnerable times in their lives is my passion. \xe2\xa0\x80
\xe2\xa0\x80
In my salon days, I became a therapist, a mentor, and a friend to many. I knew and kept secrets of everyone who sat in my chair. Back then many of us just had to seek therapy in non-traditional ways, because of lack of trust and overall economic status. Those days behind the chair definitely helped to shape my strong personality. \xe2\xa0\x80
\xe2\xa0\x80
I didn\xe2\x80\x99t create adwoa beauty because I couldn\xe2\x80\x99t find any products on the market for my natural hair. No. I created adwoa beauty because I needed a brand that not only had amazing products, but one that I could identify with and that upheld my morals and values as a human being. Values such as transparency, truth, vulnerability, and overall community. \xe2\xa0\x80
\xe2\xa0\x80
I created adwoa beauty as a brand whose mission is to help drive the black community forward by example. To provide resources, access, and, best of all, possibility. Our presence and success at Sephora will create hope for future black founders that come from where I come from, that anything is possible.\xe2\x80\x9d'

b':camera:Repost from: @briogeo "So here we are. It\xe2\x80\x99s 2020\xe2\x80\x94a year in which no one could have ever predicted, but one in which will have profound impacts on the world for years to come. As I continue to reflect on this crucial movement towards Black equality and justice, I challenge myself to find new ways for Briogeo to do its part in supporting lasting change. 
Things won't ever be "business as usual" at Briogeo because we are constantly evolving, making improvements, and finding new ways to be thoughtful about how we can make giving back an evergreen part of our business model.

We will continue to support the #blacklivesmatter and racial equality movement by increasing our financial aid to @aclu_nationwide, @blklivesmatter, and @mnfreedomfund. We will also match all employee donations to organizations that support the #blacklivesmatter movement. We will also double our commitment to our local community by providing another 50,000 meals through the Food Bank For New York City.

I want to be even more thoughtful and impactful, so I will take some time this summer to do deeper research and heart-work into what our evergreen commitment will look like. I'll report back here so that I can share with you the full plan that I feel most passionate about and that will have the most meaningful impact through our mission as a company. I want you to be part of this journey with me\xe2\x80\x94so please comment and share organizations that you feel passionate about that relate to race equality and education and empowerment for the underserved.

Thank you for the kind words of support and encouragement as I\xe2\x80\x99ve opened up and shared my story over the past few days. Aside from the opportunity to better introduce myself to the customers and fans of Briogeo, this has been a heartfelt opportunity for me to help inspire others, especially aspiring Black pioneers and entrepreneurs. I want you to know that even if you feel like the odds are stacked against you, with love, grit, passion and relentless persistence, MAGIC is possible.

The End. The Beginning. Lots of love,
Nancy"'
